               <p>GEORGE HENRY. On the 6th of June I was on <placeName id="t18270712-227-crimeloc1240">Holborn-hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270712-227-crimeloc1240" type="placeName" value="Holborn-hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270712-227-crimeloc1240" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270712-227-off1238 t18270712-227-crimeloc1240"></join>, and was called to by Murray. I then missed my handkerchief from my pocket - I found the prisoner in his custody, with it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270712-227-person1180">
                  BENJAMIN 
                  MURRAY
               <interp inst="t18270712-227-person1180" type="surname" value="MURRAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270712-227-person1180" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270712-227-person1180" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a steel-worker. On the 6th of June, the prisoner and another lad passed by me - the prisoner walked close behind Mr. Henry; his companion took the handkerchief from him, and gave it to the prisoner, who I secured with it; (the other ran away.) It was twisted round his hand; I took him to the prosecutor, who claimed it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. You took it off the pavement? A. No: it was in his hand.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
